## CSS & Classname Conventions

This project uses a hybrid approach: **semantic BEM-style classes** for structure/debugging combined with **Tailwind utilities** for styling.

### Data Attributes - REQUIRED

Every page and significant component MUST have identifying data attributes:

```tsx
// Pages - data-page attribute
<div data-page="DraftPhasePage" className="draft-page ...">

// Components - data-component attribute
<div data-component="MatchCard" data-match-id={match.id} className="match-card ...">

// State attributes for debugging
<div 
  data-component="TimerDisplay"
  data-state={isRunning ? 'running' : 'paused'}
  data-timer-value={remainingSeconds}
>
```

### BEM-Style Class Naming

Use Block__Element--Modifier pattern for semantic classes:

```tsx
// Block: The component root
className="match-card ..."

// Element: Part of the component (use double underscore)
className="match-card__header ..."
className="match-card__score-display ..."
className="match-card__player-name ..."

// Modifier: Variation of block or element (use double dash)
className="match-card--highlighted ..."
className="match-card__score-display--winner ..."
```

### Class Order Convention

Order classes consistently: **semantic first, then Tailwind utilities**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Semantic class first, then utilities
className="match-card__header flex items-center justify-between p-4"

// ❌ WRONG - Utilities first
className="flex items-center justify-between p-4 match-card__header"
```

### Required Patterns by Component Type

**Pages:**
```tsx
<div 
  data-page="PageName"
  data-state="loading" // or "ready", "error", etc.
  className="page-name min-h-screen ..."
>
  <header className="page-name__header ...">
  <main className="page-name__main ...">
  <footer className="page-name__footer ...">
</div>
```

**Interactive Components:**
```tsx
<div 
  data-component="ComponentName"
  data-selected={isSelected || undefined}
  data-disabled={isDisabled || undefined}
  className="component-name ..."
>
  <div className="component-name__content ...">
  <button className="component-name__action component-name__action--primary ...">
</div>
```

**List Items:**
```tsx
<div 
  data-component="PlayerListItem"
  data-player-id={player.id}
  data-index={index}
  className="player-list-item ..."
>
```

### Naming Guidelines

**DO:**
- Use lowercase with hyphens for class names: `match-card`, `timer-display`
- Use descriptive names that explain purpose: `score-controls`, `player-record`
- Include state modifiers: `--active`, `--disabled`, `--winner`, `--loading`
- Use data attributes for dynamic values: `data-table={tableNumber}`

**DON'T:**
- Use generic names: ~~`container`~~, ~~`wrapper`~~, ~~`box`~~
- Use camelCase in class names: ~~`matchCard`~~
- Use positional names alone: ~~`left-section`~~ → use `player-a-section`
- Mix semantic and utility in same position inconsistently

### State Classes

Use CSS classes for visual states, data attributes for JavaScript hooks:

```tsx
// Visual styling via class
className={cn(
  'match-card__player',
  isWinner && 'match-card__player--winner'
)}

// JavaScript hooks via data attribute  
data-winner={isWinner || undefined}
```

### Conditional Classes with cn()

Always use the `cn()` utility for conditional classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/cn';

className={cn(
  'base-class',
  'always-applied-utilities',
  condition && 'conditional-class',
  variant === 'primary' && 'variant--primary'
)}
```

### Component Sections

Large components should have clearly named sections:

```tsx
<div data-component="DraftPage" className="draft-page">
  {/* Header Section */}
  <header data-section="header" className="draft-page__header">
  
  {/* Main Content */}
  <main data-section="content" className="draft-page__content">
    
    {/* Pod Display */}
    <section data-section="pod" className="draft-page__pod-section">
    
    {/* Timer Display */}  
    <section data-section="timer" className="draft-page__timer-section">
    
    {/* Event Log */}
    <section data-section="event-log" className="draft-page__log-section">
  </main>
</div>
```

### Before You Commit

- [ ] All pages have `data-page` attribute
- [ ] All components have `data-component` attribute
- [ ] Semantic BEM classes come before Tailwind utilities
- [ ] State variations use `--modifier` suffix
- [ ] Dynamic values use data attributes, not class names
- [ ] No generic class names (container, wrapper, box)
